<appendix id="app.admin.docupdates">
 <title>Documentation Updates</title>
 <para>
  This chapter lists content changes for this document since the release of
  &productnamereg; 11 SP3.
 </para>
 <para>
  This manual was updated on the following dates:
 </para>
<!--list of xrefs, latest date sorted upmost-->
 <itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    <xref linkend="sec.admin.docupdates.sle12_ga" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
   </para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
 <sect1 id="sec.admin.docupdates.sle12_ga">
  <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>

  <para/>

  <variablelist>
<!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
   <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="common_docupdates_general_i.xml"/>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- Gathering System Information for Support -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.adm.support"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added the section <xref
        linkend="sec.admsupport.hostinfo"/>
        (Fate#315869).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a section about the Supportconfig Analysis (SCA) tool and
        appliance: <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.sca"/> (Fate#315699).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added the section <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.kernel"/>
        (<ulink
       url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=869159"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated and restructured the chapter.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- System Recovery and Snapshot Management with Snapper-->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.snapper"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the chapter and added new features (Fate#312751,
        Fate#316238, Fate#316233, Fate#316232, Fate#316222, Fate#316203,
        Fate#316222).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added the section <xref linkend="sec.snapper.snapshot-boot"/>
        (Fate#316231, Fate#316221, Fate#316541, Fate#316522).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.p"/> and <xref linkend="sec.y2.hw.print"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Updated chapter and section according to new CUPS version and PDF now
      being common printing data format (Fate#314630).
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--  Remote Access with VNC -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.vnc"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The default VNC viewer is now
        <systemitem
	class="resource">tigervnc</systemitem>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added corrections on window manager start-up in persistent VNC
        sessions.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- Booting a Linux System -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.boot"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Significantly shortened the chapter, because System V init has been
        replaced by systemd. systemd is now described in a separate chapter:
        <xref linkend="cha.systemd"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- The systemd daemon -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.systemd"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a new chapter on systemd and the &yast; &ycc_runlevel;
        (Fate#316631, Fate#312568).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.journalctl"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Added a new chapter
      (<ulink
       url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=878352"/>).
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- The Boot Loader GRUB 2 -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.grub2"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Replaced the GRUB legacy documentation with a new chapter on &grub;.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- The X Window System -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.x11"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the chapter to reflect dynamic configuration during each
        start-up.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated <xref linkend="sec.x11.fontsys"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- SLP -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.slp" os="sles"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Re-wrote chapter to provide significantly more information on the
        <command>slptool</command> command.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- Sharing File Systems with NFS -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.nfs"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Configuring NFSv4 shares is now mostly similar to NFSv3, especially
        the previously required bind mount setting is now deprecated
        (Fate#315589).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sles">
       <para>
        Mounting NFS volumes locally on the exporting server is not
        supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sled">
       <para>
        Removed section about NFS server configuration.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- Samba -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.samba"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added section <xref linkend="samba.advanced"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added section <xref linkend="samba.advanced.compress"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added section <xref linkend="samba.advanced.snapshots"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- On-Demand Mounting with Autofs -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.autofs"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added a chapter on <systemitem>autofs</systemitem> (Fate#316185).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- UEFI (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface) -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.uefi"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the chapter and added new features (Fate#314510,
        Fate#316365).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Fixed
        <ulink
         url="http://doccomments.provo.novell.com/comments/25080"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!-- The Apache HTTP Server -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.apache2"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed references to mono and mod_mono as it was removed from the
        distribution.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the chapter to Apache version 2.4 (Fate#316067).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed deprecated directive <literal>NameVirtualHost</literal> and
        updated <xref linkend="sec.apache2.configuration.manually.vhost"/>
        accordingly.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated <literal>Order</literal>, <literal>Allow</literal>, and
        <literal>Deny</literal> directives with standard
        <literal>Require</literal>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed virtual "Snake Oil" company from
        <xref
         linkend="sec.apache2.ssl"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- Basic Networking-->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.basicnet"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added section about new <command>wicked</command> framework for
        network configuration: <xref linkend="sec.basicnet.manconf"/>
        (Fate#316649).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Mentioned additional options that can be added to
        <filename>/etc/resolv.conf</filename>:
        <xref
         linkend="sec.basicnet.manconf.files"/> (Fate#316048).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--YaST Online Update-->
    <term><xref linkend=" cha.onlineupdate.you"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        &yast; provides an option to enable or disable the use of delta RPMs
        (Fate#314867).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Before installing patches that require a reboot, you are notified by
        &yast; and can choose how to proceed.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
<!--DHCP-->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.dhcp"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Removed dhcpcd as it is no longer shipped (Fate#316111).
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- Common Problems and Their Solutions -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.trouble"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added new section
        <xref linkend="sec.trouble.boot.btrfs"
         xrefstyle="select:title"/>
        (Fate#308679, Fate#315126).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed section about deprecated &yast; Repair module (Fate#308679).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Wi-Fi Configuration</term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Removed chapter about Wi-Fi configuration with &yast; as Wi-Fi
      configuration can be done with &nm;: <xref linkend="cha.nm"/>.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Tablet PCs</term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Removed deprecated chapter about tablet PCs.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
</appendix>
